## ✅ **Checklist**

### **Before Extraction**
- [ ] Identified cohesive method group
- [ ] Mapped all dependencies
- [ ] Estimated component size
- [ ] Chosen descriptive component name

### **During Extraction**
- [ ] Created component file with template
- [ ] Moved all related methods
- [ ] Updated imports
- [ ] Converted cache keys to private methods
- [ ] Added cleanup method if needed

### **Integration**
- [ ] Added component property to service
- [ ] Initialized in constructor
- [ ] Added cleanup to stop() method
- [ ] Created deprecated delegation methods
- [ ] Added @deprecated JSDoc annotations

### **After Extraction**
- [ ] Updated internal service usage
- [ ] Verified build passes
- [ ] Verified linting passes
- [ ] Updated tests
- [ ] Removed unused imports from main service

---

## 📊 **Success Metrics**

Track these metrics to measure success:

- **Main Service Size**: Aim for 40-50% reduction
- **Component Count**: 3-5 components ideal
- **Component Size**: 80-150 lines each
- **Test Coverage**: Maintain or improve coverage
- **Build Time**: Should not increase significantly

---

## 🎯 **Example Migration**

### **Before (Monolithic)**
```typescript
export class LevvaService extends Service {
  // 795 lines with mixed concerns
  
  async getToken() { /* token logic */ }
  async getWalletAssets() { /* wallet logic */ }
  async getCryptoNews() { /* news logic */ }
  async getBalance() { /* balance logic */ }
}
```

### **After (Component-Based)**
```typescript
// Main service - 476 lines
export class LevvaService extends Service {
  public readonly token: TokenServiceComponent;
  public readonly wallet: WalletServiceComponent;
  public readonly news: NewsServiceComponent;
  
  constructor(runtime) {
    super(runtime);
    this.token = new TokenServiceComponent(runtime);
    this.wallet = new WalletServiceComponent(runtime);
    this.news = new NewsServiceComponent(runtime);
  }
  
  /** @deprecated Use this.token.getToken() directly */
  getToken = (...args) => this.token.getToken(...args);
}

// token.ts - 150 lines
export class TokenServiceComponent {
  // Token-specific logic
}

// wallet.ts - 388 lines  
export class WalletServiceComponent extends BackgroundQueue<BalanceData> {
  // Wallet-specific logic with background queue
}

// news-component.ts - 114 lines
export class NewsServiceComponent extends BackgroundQueue<PageContent> {
  // News-specific logic with background queue
}
```

### **Results**
- ✅ 40% main service reduction (795 → 476 lines)
- ✅ 3 reusable components extracted
- ✅ Better testability
- ✅ Cleaner architecture

